snippet: Ferdinand "Ferdy" Kuebler, the first Swiss cyclist to win the Tour de France, died on Thursday in a Zurich hospital at the age of 97 following a brief illness, the Swiss Cycling federation said on its website....
lead_paragraph: Ferdinand "Ferdy" Kuebler, the first Swiss cyclist to win the Tour de France, died on Thursday in a Zurich hospital at the age of 97 following a brief illness, the Swiss Cycling federation said on its website.

headline.main: Kuebler, First Swiss Tour De France Champion, Dies at 97
headline.print_headline: Kuebler, First Swiss Tour De France Champion, Dies at 97
